cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.DL

The paper focuses on the design and evaluation of a web browser extension for knowledge workers to collect and structure information in an interactive and visual way. The paper discusses the use of automatic text analysis for content exploration, which suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the manual spatial organization of information fragments, which suggests a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses case studies with knowledge workers from different domains, which suggests a connection to cybernetics (cs.CY) and digital libraries (cs.DL).
